<http://www.spektrix.com/oldtownplayhouse/event/62601ATRDJLLGPPDCDCLHRDMCJVJGKDVB>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "9 to 5";
  schema:description """
	<h2>Music and Lyrics by Dolly Parton</h2><h2>Book by Patricia Resnick</h2>Based on the 20th Century Fox Picture<span><br/></span>Originally produced on Broadway by Robert Greenblatt, April 2009<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>When three vastly different office workers - Violet, Judy, and Doralee - are pushed to the brink by their sexist, egotistical boss, they don’t just get mad…they get even. Through a wild mix-up of fantasy, farce, and bold determination, the trio hatches a plan to take control of the office and transform their toxic work environment into a place of respect and possibility.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Directed by Michelle Perez Dungjen</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">About Tickets:</span> Tickets are $35 for Adults, $25 for Youth under 18. Please contact the Box Office if you wish to attend with a Service Dog. Discounted pricing is available for groups of 8 or more, Two-on-the-Town card holders, Military or Students with ID <span class=\"ItalicText\">only</span> by contacting the Box Office.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Content Guidance:</span> You are the best judge of what is appropriate for those you bring to the theatre, but OTP recommends this show for <a target=\"_top\" href=\" https://www.oldtownplayhouse.com/performances/plan/content-guidance.html\"> Informed Audiences</a> due to adult themes including sexual harassment, misogyny, mild sexual references, mild adult language, simulated violence, and depictions of marijuana use.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Attending a Performance:</span> We recommend that you review our <a target=\"_top\" href=\" https://www.oldtownplayhouse.com/performances/plan/\">Plan Your Visit</a> pages before purchasing tickets.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">No refunds;</span> exchanges are often possible. See our <a target=\"_top\" href=\" https://www.oldtownplayhouse.com/performances/plan/exchange-and-refund-policy.html\">Exchange and Refund Policy</a> for options if you cannot use your tickets.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">If sold out</span>, please contact the Box Office to be added to the waiting list.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">9 to 5</span> is presented through special arrangement with Music Theatre International (MTI). All authorized performance materials are also supplied by MTI.<span><br/></span>www.mtishows.com<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-09-11T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/oldtownplayhouse/files/ab38d162-257a-489b-9a30-d764fd376ebe.jpg>;
