<http://www.spektrix.com/oldtownplayhouse/event/61601AVSDPSGQNGMDBLSJQKNCHSPHMMLK>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Cosmo St. Charles is Dead and Someone in this Room Killed Him";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">by Nicole Zimmerer</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>There's one unsolved mystery that haunts Detective Mac Marlowe...and you're going to help him close the case for good! Return to the scene of the crime with Mac to relive the dinner party where renowned archeologist Cosmo St. Charles was murdered. Meet an array of unusual suspects, from Cosmo's constantly-dancing colleague to his daring airplane pilot niece. Uncover secrets...which we can't give away but let's just say they involve poisonous houseplants, twins, and the lost city of Atlantis. Choose your own adventure to help Mac unmask the murderer and try not to fall out of your chair laughing as this hilarious ode to classic murder mysteries keeps you guessing at every turn.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Performed by our <a target=\"_top\" href=\"https://www.oldtownplayhouse.com/adult-learning/aged-to-perfection.html\">Aged to Perfection</a> group in Reader's Theatre format.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Directed by Shelley Spencer</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tickets are $10, general admission. No other discounts accepted for this show. Please read our <a target=\"_top\" href=\" https://www.oldtownplayhouse.com/performances/plan/\">Plan Your Visit</a> pages before purchasing tickets.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>If sold out, please contact the OTP Box Office to be added to the waiting list.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>No refunds; exchanges often possible more than 24 hours before a performance.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Cosmo St. Charles Is Dead and Someone in This Room Killed Him</span> is produced by special arrangement with Stage Partners. (www.yourstagepartners.com)<span><br/></span>
""";
