<http://www.spektrix.com/oldtownplayhouse/event/64401AKMPPVDBDCMHSBTMJNCMMKKJJJDG>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Dracula: A Comedy of Terrors";
  schema:description """
	<h2>by Gordon Greenberg and Steve Rosen</h2>When her sister Mina falls ill with a mysterious disease of the blood, Lucy Westfeldt and her fiancé, Jonathan Harker, enlist the help of famed female vampire hunter Doctor Jean Van Helsing. Their hunt for the dangerous and sexy Count Dracula abounds with clever wordplay and quick-change antics. This lightning-fast, laugh-out-loud, gender-bending romp \"very loosely based on the novel Dracula by Bram Stoker\" is a combination of what would happen if the legendary vampire tale was put into a blender with Mel Brooks, Monty Python, and The 39 Steps!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Directed by Colleen Hill-Rakunas</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">About Tickets:</span> Tickets are $35 for Adults, $25 for Youth under 18. Please contact the Box Office if you wish to attend with a Service Dog. Discounted pricing is available for groups of 8 or more, Two-on-the-Town card holders, Military or Students with ID <span class=\"ItalicText\">only</span> by contacting the Box Office.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Content Guidance:</span> You are the best judge of what is appropriate for those you bring to the theatre, but OTP recommends this show for <a target=\"_top\" href=\" https://www.oldtownplayhouse.com/performances/plan/content-guidance.html\">General Audiences</a> despite mild sexual humor, vampire themes including biting human necks and dripping blood from the mouth.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Attending a Performance:</span> We recommend that you review our <a target=\"_top\" href=\" https://www.oldtownplayhouse.com/performances/plan/\">Plan Your Visit</a> pages before purchasing tickets.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">No refunds;</span> exchanges are often possible. See our <a target=\"_top\" href=\" https://www.oldtownplayhouse.com/performances/plan/exchange-and-refund-policy.html\">Exchange and Refund Policy</a> for options if you cannot use your tickets.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">If sold out</span>, please contact the Box Office to be added to the waiting list.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">DRACULA: A COMEDY OF TERRORS</span> is presented by arrangement with Concord Theatricals on behalf of Samuel French, Inc.<span><br/></span>www.concordtheatricals.com<span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-10-23T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/oldtownplayhouse/files/a05c9979-f956-479d-b3ef-e270c98f27ea.jpg>;
