  schema:name "Four Old Broads";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">by Leslie Kimbell</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>A mystery unfolds with laughter as four sassy seniors try to outsmart an evil nurse to figure out why residents have been moved to \"the dark side,\" what is the mysterious pill, and what happened to Doctor Head? With the Miss Magnolia Senior Citizen Pageant approaching, a cruise ship calling their name, and a retired Elvis impersonator as their sidekick, hilarity ensues for these golden gals as they piece together clues.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>You are the best judge of what is appropriate for those you bring to the theatre, but OTP recommends this show for Informed Audiences due to mild sexual humor and mild drug humor.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Directed by: Caroline Haugen</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tickets are $35 for Adults, $25 for Youth under 18. Please read our <a target=\"_top\" href=\"https://www.oldtownplayhouse.com/performances/plan/\">Plan Your Visit</a> page before purchasing tickets.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Please call the Box Office for discounted pricing: Partial View seats, Groups of 8 or more, Two-on-the-Town card holders, Military or Students with ID, or if you wish to attend with a Service Dog.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>If sold out, please contact the OTP Box Office to be added to the waiting list.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>No refunds; exchanges often possible more than 24 hours before a performance.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>FOUR OLD BROADS is presented by arrangement with Concord Theatricals on behalf of Samuel French, Inc. www.concordtheatricals.com<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
