<http://www.spektrix.com/oldtownplayhouse/event/25001ADDVSKQBVSNBTBDPCMQTVGBHJDPN>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Misery";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">by William Goldman<span><br/></span>Based on the novel by Stephen King</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Successful romance novelist Paul Sheldon is rescued from a car crash by his number one fan, Annie, and wakes up captive in her secluded home. While he is convalescing, she reads the manuscript to his newest novel and becomes enraged to discover the author has killed off her favorite character. Annie forces Paul to write a new novel, and he quickly realizes Annie has no intention of letting him leave.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>You are the best judge of what is appropriate for those you bring to the theatre, but OTP recommends this show for Mature Audiences due to language, violence, gore, and brutal murder scenes.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Directed by: Karla Morner Fishburn</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tickets are $35 for Adults, $25 for Youth under 18. Please read our <a target=\"_top\" href=\"https://www.oldtownplayhouse.com/performances/plan/\">Plan Your Visit</a> page before purchasing tickets.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Please call the Box Office for discounted pricing: Partial View seats, Groups of 8 or more, Two-on-the-Town card holders, Military or Students with ID, or if you wish to attend with a Service Dog.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>If sold out, please contact the OTP Box Office to be added to the waiting list.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>No refunds; exchanges often possible more than 24 hours before a performance.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Original Broadway production produced by Warner Bros. Theatre Ventures in association with Castle Rock Entertainment, Liz Glotzer, Mark Kaufman, Martin Shafer, Raymond Wu<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>World Premiere produced at Bucks County Playhouse, New Hope, PA (Jed Bernstein, Producing Director)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>MISERY is presented by special arrangement with Broadway Licensing, LLC, service the Dramatists Play Service collection (www.dramatists.com).<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
