<http://www.spektrix.com/oldtownplayhouse/event/21801ABPGGTNVQRGNRTJRVPPDJJQDTSQC>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Once Upon a Mattress";
  schema:description """
	Princess Winnifred, an unconventional and spirited woman, vies for the hand of Prince Dauntless, but must pass a test devised by his domineering mother, Queen Aggravain. Full of humor, quirky characters, and catchy songs, this comedic musical retelling of the classic fairy tale <span class=\"ItalicText\">The Princess and the Pea</span> is a lighthearted tale of love and defying expectations.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Green Cast performs: June 5, June 6 (7pm), June 11, June 13 (2pm)<span><br/></span>Gold Cast performs: June 6 (2pm),  June 7 (2pm), June 12, June 13 (7pm)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tickets are $22 for Adults, $15 for Youth under 18. Please read our <a target=\"_top\" href=\"https://www.oldtownplayhouse.com/performances/plan/\">Plan Your Visit</a> page before purchasing tickets.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Performer Families:</span> Complimentary tickets (2 per performer) are available when tuition is paid to the person that paid the tuition. We cannot issue refunds for any tickets purchased, though we can make exchanges.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Please call the Box Office for discounted pricing: Obstructed View seats, Groups of 8 or more, Two-on-the-Town card holders, or if you wish to attend with a Service Dog.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>If sold out, please contact the OTP Box Office to be added to the waiting list.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>No refunds; exchanges often possible more than 24 hours before a performance.<span><br/></span>
""";
