<http://www.spektrix.com/oldtownplayhouse/event/17401ARMGDGRGTJBKVPBLJVRHCKNDGPTT>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Pan! (Theatre Explorers)";
  schema:description """
	In this adventure-packed show you'll meet the dog Nana, who can't stop the Darling children from following Peter and Tinkerbell through the nursery open window to Neverland. There, they make friends with the Lost Boys and Princess Tiger Lily as they encounter Captain Hook, his gang of wily pirates, and of course, the ticking crocodile.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Performed by student campers from our 1-week Theatre Explorers camp.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Note that these performances are at The MATCH, in the Cherryland Mall, 1728 S. Garfield Ave, Traverse City (entrance near the old K-Mart entrance).<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tickets are $22 for Adults, $15 for Youth under 18. Please read our <a target=\"_top\" href=\"https://www.oldtownplayhouse.com/performances/plan-your-visit.html\">Plan Your Visit</a> page before purchasing tickets.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Performer Families:</span> Complimentary tickets (2 per performer) are available when tuition is paid to the person that paid the tuition. We cannot issue refunds for any tickets purchased, though we can make exchanges.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Please call the Box Office for discounted pricing: Groups of 8 or more, Two-on-the-Town card holders, or if you wish to attend with a Service Dog.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>If sold out, we have a waiting list.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2025-06-27T18:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
