<http://www.spektrix.com/oldtownplayhouse/event/51601ASNDVBQVGLKLVCBQNQGNVJJTVQBG>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Robin Hood: Naught in Nottingham Spring Break Performance";
  schema:description """
	In this uproarious version of the classic tale, anachronisms abound, paninis are pressed, and of course the outlaws outfox the bad guys. Meet Robin and the whole gang as you've never seen them before. There’s merriment galore at the world’s first Renaissance Fair with horseless jousting, goofy disguises, silly chases, and epic battles with pool noodles!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Performed by student campers from our 1-week Spring Break camp.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Note that these performances are at The MATCH, in the Cherryland Mall, 1728 S. Garfield Ave, Traverse City (entrance near the old K-Mart entrance).<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tickets are $22 for Adults, $15 for Youth under 18. Please read our Plan Your Visit page before purchasing tickets. We cannot issue refunds for any tickets purchased, though we can make exchanges.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Please call the Box Office for discounted pricing: Groups of 8 or more, Two-on-the-Town card holders, or if you wish to attend with a Service Dog.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>If sold out, we have a waiting list.
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-04-04T14:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
