<http://www.spektrix.com/oldtownplayhouse/event/71601AMRKGCHRRTHJRLKKPCDSPHMKGQPR>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Sophocles' Antigone";
  schema:description """
	<h2>Adapted by Bonnie Roberts</h2>From a play by Sophocles<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>A civil war has ended. Will there be peace or new rebellion? What if your family, your friends, everyone you cared about begged you to change your mind, begged you to be silent - be safe? What if your life was in danger because of a decision you made, an action you decided to take? Would you be willing to die for taking that action? Or would you refuse the responsibility of making that decision? Each Greek Chorus member argues the side of one of the characters, hoping, this time, to bring understanding and peace to the war-torn land. There are no heroes, no villains here. Only individuals who face the choice: should I do what I feel is right? Or should I stay silent and safe? <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">About Tickets:</span> Tickets are $15. Please contact the Box Office if you wish to attend with a Service Dog.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Content Guidance:</span> You are the best judge of what is appropriate for those you bring to the theatre, but OTP recommends this show for <a target=\"_top\" href=\" https://www.oldtownplayhouse.com/performances/plan/content-guidance.html\">Informed Audiences</a> due to themes of moral conflict and violence.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Attending a Performance:</span> We recommend that you review our <a target=\"_top\" href=\" https://www.oldtownplayhouse.com/performances/plan/\">Plan Your Visit</a> pages before purchasing tickets.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">No refunds;</span> exchanges are often possible. See our <a target=\"_top\" href=\" https://www.oldtownplayhouse.com/performances/plan/exchange-and-refund-policy.html\">Exchange and Refund Policy</a> for options if you cannot use your tickets.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">If sold out</span>, please contact the Box Office to be added to the waiting list.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Produced by special arrangement with THE DRAMATIC PUBLISHING COMPANY of Woodstock, Illinois<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
