<http://www.spektrix.com/oldtownplayhouse/event/34001AGQQHTLTHTMBJQGPRQRMLLBGHNMV>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Studio Factory Double Feature";
  schema:description """
	This double-feature has two one-act plays:<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Youth Studio Factory</span> performs <span class=\"ItalicText\">Folk Tails:</span> Monkeys and turtles and coyotes - oh, my! A group of narrators come together to tell international folk tales introducing young audiences to <span class=\"ItalicText\">The Monkey's Heart</span> from India, <span class=\"ItalicText\">Anansi's Dinner Guest</span> from the Ashanti people of Ghana, <span class=\"ItalicText\">The Bremen Town Musicians</span> based in Germany, <span class=\"ItalicText\">Coyote Gets Revenge</span> from the Chippewa people of North America, as well as other Asian and African folk tales.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Teen Studio Factory</span> performs <span class=\"ItalicText\">Bad Auditions by Bad Actors:</span> A casting director has one day to find the leads for a community theater production of Romeo and Juliet. But what seems like a simple task proves impossible when the pool of actors includes extreme method actors, performers who just don't know what to do with their hands, and one particular woman who may or may not think she's a cat. This hilarious comedy will bring you to the last place you'd ever want to be...behind the doors of a casting session.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Note that these performances are at The MATCH, in the Cherryland Mall, 1728 S. Garfield Ave, Traverse City (entrance near the old K-Mart entrance).<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tickets are $22 for Adults, $15 for Youth under 18. Please read our <a target=\"_top\" href=\"https://www.oldtownplayhouse.com/performances/plan-your-visit.html\">Plan Your Visit</a> page before purchasing tickets.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Performer Families:</span> Complimentary tickets (2 per performer) are available when tuition is paid to the person that paid the tuition. We cannot issue refunds for any tickets purchased, though we can make exchanges.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Please call the Box Office for discounted pricing: Obstructed View seats, Groups of 8 or more, Two-on-the-Town card holders, or if you wish to attend with a Service Dog.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>If sold out, we have a waiting list.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>No refunds; exchanges often possible more than 24 hours before a performance.<span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2025-08-01T19:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/oldtownplayhouse/files/2f2d5bab-21b0-4df7-814c-8fcc72058bbd.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/oldtownplayhouse/location/1601APDLPHDNDHQKCQVBHMDTSQVKMKLPQ>;
