  schema:name "The Hobbit";
  schema:description """
	Bilbo Baggins is a shy hobbit who is unexpectedly thrust into an epic adventure with a group of dwarves. Their quest to reclaim a stolen treasure from the fearsome dragon Smaug takes them through dangerous lands, facing trolls, goblins and giant spiders. Along the way, Bilbo discovers bravery, friendship and his true potential, ultimately playing a pivotal role in the battle for the treasure.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Directed by Leo Bevington</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tickets are $22 for Adults, $15 for Youth under 18. Please read our <a target=\"_top\" href=\"https://www.oldtownplayhouse.com/performances/plan-your-visit.html\">Plan Your Visit</a> page before purchasing tickets.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Performer Families:</span> Complimentary tickets (2 per performer) are available when tuition is paid to the person that paid the tuition. We cannot issue refunds for any tickets purchased, though we can make exchanges.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Please call the Box Office for discounted pricing: Obstructed View seats, Groups of 8 or more, Two-on-the-Town card holders, or if you wish to attend with a Service Dog.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>If sold out, please contact the OTP Box Office to be added to the waiting list.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>No refunds; exchanges often possible more than 24 hours before a performance.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
