<http://www.spektrix.com/oldtownplayhouse/event/29601AVVVGLGMQTHTLNRNLGJBCQJTVHSN>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "The Minutes";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">by Tracy Letts</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>When a newly elected council member, Mr. Peel, returns to his first meeting after being absent due to a family death, he finds a fellow council member, Mr. Carp, is missing and that the minutes from the previous week are gone, sparking his investigation into the town's hidden, dark history. This play is an exploration of American politics and the fragility of local government, revealing hidden truths and cracks in the surface of seemingly ordinary life in a small town.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>You are the best judge of what is appropriate for those you bring to the theatre, but OTP recommends this show for Informed Audiences due to language, political discourse, and disagreements throughout, including depictions of Native American histories and inaccuracies.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Directed by: Aaron Wineman</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tickets are $25. Please read our <a target=\"_top\" href=\"https://www.oldtownplayhouse.com/performances/plan-your-visit.html\">Plan Your Visit</a> page before purchasing tickets.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Please call the Box Office for discounted pricing: Groups of 8 or more, Two-on-the-Town card holders, Military or Students with ID, or if you wish to attend with a Service Dog.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>If sold out, please contact the OTP Box Office to be added to the waiting list.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>No refunds; exchanges often possible more than 24 hours before a performance.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>\"The Minutes\" is presented by arrangement with Concord Theatricals on behalf of Samuel French, Inc.  www.concordtheatricals.com<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
