<http://www.spektrix.com/oldtownplayhouse/event/11601ASNTDDTNQDPTRBBMHTCLMHBVDMHV>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "The Prince of Egypt";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"ItalicText\">The Prince of Egypt</span> is an exciting musical that promises to delight audiences of all ages. Based on the beloved, Oscar-winning DreamWorks Animation film, you'll journey through the wonders of Ancient Egypt as Ramses and Moses, two young men raised together as brothers in a kingdom of privilege, find themselves suddenly divided by a secret past. One must rule as Pharaoh, the other must rise up and free his true people; both face a destiny that will change history forever. <span class=\"ItalicText\">The Prince of Egypt</span> is a sweeping epic with music and lyrics by Grammy and Oscar winner Stephen Schwartz, a book by Philip LaZebnik, and 10 new songs written by Schwartz, together with five of his songs from the film. The show also features Schwartz’s Academy Award-winning song, “When You Believe.”<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Directed by Wes Curry</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Getting Tickets</h2><span><br/></span>Tickets are $48 for Adults, $25 for Youth under 18 (fees are included in these prices). When purchasing 6 or more tickets in one order, use the <span class=\"BoldText\">Summer6</span> promotion code for a $6 discount on each ticket in your order. This promotion may only be used on a single order, not on multiple orders that add up to 6 or more tickets, and it may not be applied retroactively. No other discounts, OTP complimentary tickets, or OTP complimentary gift certificates may be used for this production.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>No refunds; exchanges often possible more than 24 hours before a performance.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>If sold out, please contact the OTP Box Office to be added to the waiting list.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Attending a Performance</h2><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Doors</span> open 1 hour before the performance. <span class=\"BoldText\">Seating</span> begins 30 minutes prior to the performance. <span class=\"BoldText\">Concessions</span> are available in the lobby 1 hour before the performance.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Parking</span>: The Aspen lot is closest to the Milliken Auditorium, though because classes at NMC are not in session during the performances, the entire campus is permit-free, so you may park anywhere.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
