<http://www.spektrix.com/oldtownplayhouse/event/67001APKGPVRDVBKMDCRCRMPHDNRDBKDN>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "The Tragedy of Macbeth";
  schema:description """
	<h2>by William Shakespeare</h2>A tragedy about a Scottish nobleman whose blind ambition, spurred by three witches' prophecies and his wife, leads him to murder King Duncan and seize the throne. Plagued by guilt and paranoia, Macbeth becomes a tyrant, committing more murders to secure his power before being defeated and killed by Macduff, restoring order.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Directed by Leo Buzzell-Bevington</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">About Tickets:</span> Tickets are $35 for Adults, $25 for Youth under 18. Please contact the Box Office if you wish to attend with a Service Dog. Discounted pricing is available for groups of 8 or more, Two-on-the-Town card holders, Military or Students with ID <span class=\"ItalicText\">only</span> by contacting the Box Office.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Content Guidance:</span> You are the best judge of what is appropriate for those you bring to the theatre, but OTP recommends this show for <a target=\"_top\" href=\" https://www.oldtownplayhouse.com/performances/plan/content-guidance.html\">General Audiences</a> despite murder most foul, the death of a child, an instance of suicide, violence.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Attending a Performance:</span> We recommend that you review our <a target=\"_top\" href=\" https://www.oldtownplayhouse.com/performances/plan/\">Plan Your Visit</a> pages before purchasing tickets.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">No refunds;</span> exchanges are often possible. See our <a target=\"_top\" href=\" https://www.oldtownplayhouse.com/performances/plan/exchange-and-refund-policy.html\">Exchange and Refund Policy</a> for options if you cannot use your tickets.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">If sold out</span>, please contact the Box Office to be added to the waiting list.<span><br/></span>
""";
