<http://www.spektrix.com/oldtownplayhouse/event/29401ADJVTMPMVSKRPCKNPVMCRPLRQJRR>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Whose Life is it Anyway?";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">by Brian Clark</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Ken Harrison, a successful sculptor, is paralyzed and kept alive by support systems. Outwardly he's cheerful and often very funny, but he's overwhelmed by the fact that he has lost control of his own life. Harrison decides that he does not want to live only to exist as a medical achievement. However, his physician is determined to preserve Harrison's life regardless of its quality.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>You are the best judge of what is appropriate for those you bring to the theatre, but OTP recommends this show for Informed Audiences due to assisted suicide in a medical setting, instances of minor sexual situations and discussions.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Directed by Don Kuehlhorn</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tickets are $25. Please read our <a target=\"_top\" href=\"https://www.oldtownplayhouse.com/performances/plan-your-visit.html\">Plan Your Visit</a> page before purchasing tickets.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Please call the Box Office for discounted pricing: Groups of 8 or more, Two-on-the-Town card holders, Military or Students with ID, or if you wish to attend with a Service Dog.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>If sold out, please contact the OTP Box Office to be added to the waiting list.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>No refunds; exchanges often possible more than 24 hours before a performance.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Produced by special arrangement with THE DRAMATIC PUBLISHING COMPANY of Woodstock, Illinois<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
